Simmer down, Mr. Lu. She's nice.

122
00:07:43,397 --> 00:07:44,957
- Peaches.
- Keling.

123
00:07:46,998 --> 00:07:49,198
Peilan, have you heard
that someone stole children

124
00:07:49,238 --> 00:07:50,357
near Guantou Temple?

125
00:07:51,118 --> 00:07:52,837
No, I haven't.

126
00:07:52,837 --> 00:07:54,998
Once I catch them,
I'll teach them a lesson.

127
00:07:58,357 --> 00:08:00,558
Wait. Can you finish them
as you took so many peaches?

128
00:08:01,277 --> 00:08:03,998
Mother. I'm leaving.

129
00:08:04,878 --> 00:08:05,998
Where are you going, Keling?

130
00:08:06,118 --> 00:08:07,680
To study.

131
00:08:16,118 --> 00:08:17,536
That girl.

132
00:08:25,198 --> 00:08:26,784
She drove me crazy.

133
00:08:35,837 --> 00:08:36,957
Have you eaten yet?

134
00:08:37,357 --> 00:08:38,880
Not yet.

135
00:08:40,717 --> 00:08:43,198
Well, this is for you.

136
00:08:44,757 --> 00:08:46,558
No, thanks. Mr. Lu, you eat it.

137
00:08:47,678 --> 00:08:48,837
How about I break it open?

138
00:08:49,198 --> 00:08:50,318
We can share it.

139
00:08:52,477 --> 00:08:53,318
It's okay, Mr. Lu.

140
00:08:53,398 --> 00:08:55,717
I don't want to eat it now. You eat it.

141
00:08:58,278 --> 00:09:00,158
What family members are they?

142
00:09:00,798 --> 00:09:01,717
It is your birthday today,

143
00:09:01,717 --> 00:09:02,798
but an extra peach isn't saved.

144
00:09:03,278 --> 00:09:06,518
It's not like that.
They have their own business.

145
00:09:07,198 --> 00:09:08,158
And it's just a birthday.

146
00:09:09,237 --> 00:09:10,158
Not a big deal.

147
00:09:16,038 --> 00:09:20,357
Forget it. Have this half.

148
00:09:30,498 --> 00:09:33,344
